{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/2486/comments/26165432.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/diff/osrf/gazebo:39b01cdaec7d..ec2881681a3e?path=gazebo%2Frendering%2FLight.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2486/_/diff#comment-26165432"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 2486, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/2486.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2486"}}, "title": "Fix light cast shadows"}, "content": {"raw": "I just recently learned about this and ticketed issue #2083. I wonder if there's a nice way to make users aware of this, maybe a warning we can print somewhere... Or always return false for `Light::CastShadows` for certain types, and also display it as false on the GUI...", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I just recently learned about this and ticketed issue <a href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/2083/point-and-spot-lights-dont-cast-shadows\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Point and spot lights don&#39;t cast shadows\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#2083</a>. I wonder if there's a nice way to make users aware of this, maybe a warning we can print somewhere... Or always return false for <code>Light::CastShadows</code> for certain types, and also display it as false on the GUI...</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-11-02T16:12:15.766044+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-4